# Week-3-Day-05
Responsive Design
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Responsive Layout</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        .header {
            width: 100%;
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2%;
        }

        .navbar {
            width: 100%;
            background-color: #34495e;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1%;
        }

        .navbar a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 2%;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .container {
            width: 100%;
            display: flex;
        }

        .sidebar {
            width: 30%;
            background-color: #ecf0f1;
            padding: 2%;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        .content {
            width: 70%;
            padding: 2%;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        .footer {
            width: 100%;
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2%;
        }

        /* Mobile View */
        @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {

            .container {
                flex-direction: column;
            }

            .sidebar {
                width: 100%;
            }

            .content {
                width: 100%;
            }

            .navbar a {
                display: block;
                margin: 2% 0;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <div class="header">
        <h1>Responsive Layout</h1>
        <p>Using Percentage Width and Media Queries</p>
    </div>

    <div class="navbar">
        <a href="#">Home</a>
        <a href="#">About</a>
        <a href="#">Services</a>
        <a href="#">Contact</a>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="sidebar">
            <h2>Sidebar</h2>
            <p>This sidebar uses 30% width on desktop view.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content">
            <h2>Main Content</h2>
            <p>This content area uses 70% width on desktop view.</p>
            <p>On mobile screens, both sections become 100% width.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <p>© 2026 Responsive Layout </p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
